{
  "texts": [
    "• wij represents the weight of the connection between neuron i and the j-th input.",
    "• xj represents the j-th attribute value of the input instance.",
    "• bi represents the bias term associated with neuron i.The output value of neuron i after applying the activation function f is:",
    "The final output of the ANN is typically the output of the last neuron in the output layer, which can be interpreted as a probability score.",
    "To classify an instance, we may apply a threshold (e.g., 0.5) to the output score to assign a binary label."
  ]
}